summary: An FBI 302 interview report documenting an interview conducted on July 31, 2019, with an individual who denied any knowledge of Jeffrey Epstein. The interview took place at the NYPD's 13th Precinct in Long Island City, Queens, New York.

persons.name: Jeffrey Epstein
persons.context: The individual being interviewed was shown a photo of Epstein and denied knowing him.

events.title: FBI Interview at NYPD Precinct
events.description: An FBI agent interviewed an individual at the NYPD's 13th Precinct in Long Island City, New York, regarding knowledge of Jeffrey Epstein.

locations: New York Police Department's 13th Precinct, 4707 Pearson Place, Long Island City, Queens, New York
keyFacts: An individual was interviewed by the FBI on July 31, 2019, and denied any knowledge of Jeffrey Epstein.
The individual was shown a photograph of Jeffrey Epstein and stated she did not know him.
The interview was conducted at the NYPD's 13th Precinct in Long Island City, Queens, New York.
The individual's personal history includes attending high school in Queens, moving to Brazil, then to San Diego, CA, and returning to New York in 2005.
